messageBody:
Ted Larson Freeman scripsit:

> Read went with Choice 2 for SQUARE, so if we interpret his spelling of
> "mere" as Choice 1 for NEAR, then it means these choices (and that for
> CURE) are not necessarily so tightly coupled.

Sure. I just proposed them that way in order to get six choices
down to two.

--
John Cowan cowan@... http://ccil.org/~cowan

nature of a fact is not a justification for attributing it to powers
above nature. --The Catholic Encyclopedia, s.v. "telepathy" (1913)
